@NODE "DownLoad" "What is this stuff?"

@{par}                             @{fg shine}What is this stuff?@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}The original archive should contain the following files:
@{par}
@{par} @{fg fill}@{"ARexx (dir)        " LINK "ARexx" }
@{par} @{"c (dir)            " LINK "c"     }
@{par} @{"Color&Pointer (dir)" LINK "C&P"   }
@{par} @{"Drives (dir)       " LINK "Drives"}
@{par} @{"Fonts (dir)        " LINK "Fonts" }
@{par} @{"Icons (dir)        " LINK "Icons" }
@{par} @{"Images (dir)       " LINK "Images"}
@{par} @{"Patterns (dir)     " LINK "Patterns"}
@{par} @{"WBStartup (dir)    " LINK "WBStartup"}@{fg text}
@{par}  ARexx.info                       @{b}Button_Template@{ub}
@{par}  Button_Template.info             C.info
@{par}  Color&Pointer.info               DirectoryOpus.info
@{par}  @{b}DOpusScreen.pic@{ub}                  DOpusScreen.pic.info
@{par}  Drives.info                      Fonts.info
@{par}  Icons.info                       Images.info
@{par}  @{b}MWB_DOpus.guide@{ub}                  MWB_DOpus.guide.info
@{par}  @{b}NudelScreen.pic@{ub}                  NudelScreen.pic.info
@{par}  Patterns.info                    @{b}SYSOPS.README@{ub}
@{par}  SYSOPS.README.info               WBStartup.info
@{par}
@{par}The @{b}Button_Template@{ub} is just a picture of everything in the @{"images drawer" LINK "Images"} as
well as some extra stuff (it's handy as a template for drawing your own,
but if you do, make sure you upload them for everyone else to enjoy!)
@{par}
@{par}@{b}DOpusScreen.pic@{ub} is a snapshot of @{"my" LINK "Author"} DOpus screen which may give you some
ideas!
@{par}
@{par}@{b}NudelScreen.pic@{ub} is a snapshot of @{"Leo Davidson's" LINK "Author"} DOpus screen (even more
ideas for you A500 owners ;)
@{par}
@{par}@{b}MWB_DOpus5.guide@{ub} - you are reading it ;)
@{par}
@{par}@{b}SYSOPS.README@{ub} is just a notice to BBS sysops regarding the naming convension
of this archive to try to avoid the situation where people accidentally
download the same archive twice (or more) because it has a different name.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "ARexx" "ARexx (dir)"
@TOC "Download"

@{par}                                  @{fg shine}ARexx (dir)@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}This dir contains the following ARexx scripts written by @{"Leo Davidson" LINK "Author"}:
@{par}
@{par}  @{b}WinCopy.dopus5@{ub}                   WinCopy.dopus5.info
@{par}  @{b}WinSwap.dopus5@{ub}                   WinSwap.dopus5.info
@{par}
@{par}Copy them into your @{b}DOpus5:Arexx/@{ub} drawer. Read their headers for configuration
information and discription.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "c" "c"
@TOC "Download"

@{par}                               @{fg shine}The "c" directory@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}This dir contains the following items:
@{par}
@{par} @{"DIF" LINK "DIF"}                          DIF.info
@{par} DIF.readme                    DIF.readme.info
@{par} @{"PaletteShove" LINK "PS"}                 PaletteShove.info
@{par} PaletteShove.guide            PaletteShove.guide.info

@ENDNODE

@NODE "C&P" "Color&Pointer"
@TOC "Download"

@{par}                                 @{fg shine}Color&Pointer@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}This drawer contains the following:
@{par}
@{par} ClickForColors                   ClickForColors.info
@{par} ClickForPointer                  ClickForPointer.info
@{par}
@{par}These are just my palette and pointer configs. Clicking on them will change
your prefs to emulate mine - but only until you reboot. The palette is quite
useful, as most times I draw things to look good using my palette (of course)
and it may not necessarily look good with yours!?

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Drives" "Drives"
@TOC "Download"

@{par}                                    @{fg shine}Drives@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}This archive contains the following drive brushes:
@{par}
@{par} Plain.brush                      Plain.info
@{par} Work.brush                       Work.info
@{par} System.brush                     System.info
@{par}
@{par}I intended to use these to make a drive bank, however DOpus put a significant
sized border around them - which defeated the original purpose of making them
small! However, you may still find a use for them!?

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Fonts" "Fonts"
@TOC "DownLoad"

@{par}                                     @{fg shine}Fonts@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}This directory just contains a couple of fonts which some of you might like
to use for DOpus? Check out the NOoDLE & P0T fonts by @{"Leo Davidson" LINK "Author"}.
@{par}
@{par} @{fg fill}P0T-IBM (dir)
@{par} P0T-NOoDLE (dir)
@{par} P0T-Prop (dir)
@{par} PolarSmall-Prop (dir)
@{par} PolarSmall (dir)@{fg text}
@{par} P0T-IBM.font                     P0T-NOoDLE.font
@{par} P0T-Prop.font                    PolarSmall-Prop.font
@{par} PolarSmall.font

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Icons" "Icons"
@TOC "Download"

@{par}                                     @{fg shine}Icons@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}This archive contains the following icons:
@{par}
@{par} AppIcon.info                     Buttons.info
@{par} Environment.info                 Filetype.info
@{par} Group.info                       Lister.info
@{par} Settings.info
@{par}
@{par}I realize that these may look identical to the ones supplied with DOpus, but
they have been fixed. The original icons @{i}swim@{ui} when you click on them - there
were gliches in them which I fixed (I don't know why - it just bugged me I
guess!?! ;)

@ENDNODE

