@{par}
@{par}The @{b}ClassicMarble@{ub} and @{b}Paper@{ub} were obtained from other archives, however, I fixed
them so they repeated properly. The @{b}DOpusStone#_LoRes@{ub} patterns were designed by
@{"Leo" LINK "Author"} for all you people with LoRes screens (the # indicates the number of DOpus
hedgehogs on the pattern).

@ENDNODE

@NODE "WBStartup" "WBStartup"
@TOC "Download"

@{par}                                   @{fg shine}WBStartup@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}This archive includes the following items in the WBStartup drawer:
@{par}
@{par} Opus5_Startup                    Opus5_Startup.info
@{par}
@{par}I've just put this here, because I think that the icon I drew for the
Opus5_Startup is better than the one which is provided (you may not?).

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements" "System Requirements..."

@{par}                            @{fg shine}System Requirements...@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}Since this archive requires DOpus5, you must have the minimum requirements as
stated in the DOpus5 manual: KickStart 2.04 or higher, 1 Meg RAM, and a Hard Drive.
However, a recommended configuration@{b}°@{ub} includes 4 Meg RAM and at least a 68030.
@{par}
@{par}@{b}°@{ub}Recommendation by Amiga Computing's Frank Nord - Issue 88, page 33.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Installation" "Installation"

@{par}                                 @{fg shine}Installation@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}If anyone thinks that this archive requires an installation script then mail
me. I think most people would actually prefer to install this stuff themselves.
@{par}
@{par}All you need to do is copy this stuff where you want it. One recommendation,
however would be to rename the images drawer in DOpus5: to something else and
then copy the included images drawer into DOpus5: (since this is where DOpus
looks for icons be default).
@{par}
@{par}If the brushes and pictures are not compliant with your palette then you will
want to use @{"DIF" LINK "DIF"} (possibly in conjunction with @{"PaletteShove" LINK "PS"}) - both programs and
their respective documentation are included in this archive in @{"c (dir)" LINK "C"}).
@{par}
@{par}As for the @{"pictures and the guide" LINK "DownLoad"}, you can delete them when you're done with
them (although you might like to hang on to the @{"Buttons_Template" LINK "DownLoad"} which will
serve as a good template for drawing your own icons and an index when you are
not sure which icon to pick).

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HintsTips" "Hints & Tips & HELP!"
@NEXT "HintsTips"

@{par}                             @{fg shine}Hints & Tips & HELP!@{fg fill}
@{par}
@{par} · If you decide to use the included toolbar icons, it is a good idea to delete
@{par}   or rename the @{b}default images drawer@{ub} in @{b}DOpus5:@{ub}. Then copy the @{"Images" LINK "Images"} drawer
@{par}   included in this archive into your @{b}DOpus5:@{ub} directory (since this is where
@{par}   DOpus looks for images by default).
@{par}
@{par} · If you want to make a drive bank (similar to DOpus4) you can use a button
@{par}   bank with the @{b}ScanDir@{ub} command (see my @{"DOpusScreen.pic" LINK "DownLoad"}).
@{par}@{fg text}
@{par} · Is it possible to have drive icons on the DOpus screen which do not
@{par}   necessarily exist on WorkBench? For instance, for an assign?
@{par}@{fg fill}
@{par}   -> Answered by @{"Leo Davidson" LINK "Author"}: You can @{b}leave out@{ub} any directory, so long as
@{par}      it has an ICON. Directories left out on the DOpus screen are @{b}NOT@{ub} left
@{par}      out on the Workbench (unless you also leave them out on the Workbench).
@{par}      BUT, you can't leave things out which do not have an icon.
@{par}@{fg text}
@{par} · Is everyone having the same problems I am with snapshoting icons in DOpus..
@{par}   wherever you snapshot the windows in DOpus is where they end up on the
@{par}   workbench? Am I doing something wrong?
@{par}@{fg fill}
@{par}   -> Answered by @{"Leo Davidson" LINK "Author"}: Yes, there is currently no way around this :(
@{par}@{fg text}
@{par} · What happened to the SWAPDIR and COPYDIR commands? Is there a way to
@{par}   impliment this through other commands (to operate on the source and the
@{par}   destination)?
@{par}@{fg fill}
@{par}   -> Answered by @{"Greg Perry" LINK "LeoD5PM_OrderInfo"}: the COPYWIN command may be envoked via ARexx.
@{par}@{fg text}
@{par} · Does it annoy anyone else that when you click on the button banks that they
@{par}   remain highlighted and then you have to go back and click on the window?
@{par}   Once the operation has been preformed, the window in which the action was
@{par}   preformed should be rehighlighted...right?
@{par}
@{par} · Can you save the prefs so that the clock remains ON?
@{par}@{fg fill}
@{par}   -> Answered by @{"Leo Davidson" LINK "Author"}: Yes, but you must quit DOpus for the changes to
@{par}      remain in effect.
@{par}@{fg text}
@{par} · I wish you could get rid of the borders on the button banks...what a waste
@{par}   of space (it would nice to have a feature like ToolManager)!
@{par}
@{par} · How do you replace the cycle gadget in the ToolBarLister?
@{par}@{fg fill}
@{par}   -> Answered by @{"Leo Davidson" LINK "Author"}: See @{"Images" LINK "Images"} - at the bottom of the page, there
@{par}      is a note on how to replace the cycle gadget.
@{par}
@{par} · Here are a couple of great tips from @{"Leo Davidson" LINK "Author"}:
@{par}   @{"How to add an LHA destination-path file-requester to a button (or menu)    " LINK "LHADest"}
@{par}   @{"An LHA button (or menu) which creates seperate directories for each archive" LINK "LHADir"}
@{par}@{fg text}
@{par} · Why do all screens remap whenever you change resolution (i.e. in paint
@{par}   programs) whenever DOpus is running? For instance if you change the page
@{par}   size in OpalPaint while the DOpus window is open then Workbench remaps it's
@{par}   screen, however if DOpus is iconified this doesn't happen (it is very
@{par}   annoying and it slows things down!).
@{par}
@{par} · In order to play @{b}The Settlers@{ub} (© BlueByte), you must kill DOpus or your
@{par}   machine goes Balistic (WHY, does it have something to do will the PAL mode?)
@{par}
@{par} · Push this button @{b}->@{ub} @{bg fill}@{" " LINK "GURU"}@{bg background} to see a crash which @{"MCP (© ALiEN DESiGN)" LINK "MCP"} reported:
@{par}   Can anyone tell me what it mean?
@{par}@{fg fill}
@{par}   -> Answered by @{"Greg Perry" LINK "LeoD5PM_OrderInfo"}: GPSoftware believes these bugs have been fixed
@{par}      for 5.11 (available on Aminet).
@{par}@{fg text}
@{par} · When you load DOpus after bootup, one window becomes the source and the
@{par}   other becomes the destination (that is good); however if you launch DOpus
@{par}   from the WBStartup, then both windows are off when you deiconify it (is
@{par}   there someway to fix this...if not what the hell is the good of that...
@{par}   I mean when I open DOpus I obviously want to use it, so why should I have
@{par}   to click on both windows to get the source and destination?)
@{par}
@{par} · Where do you put the PublicScreen name for the {Qs} delimiter? I've tried:
@{par}   command {@{b}Qs@{ub}Workbench}
@{par}   command {@{b}Qs@{ub}"Workbench"}
@{par}   command {@{b}Qs@{ub}}Workbench
@{par}   command {@{b}Qs@{ub}}"Workbench"
@{par}   but none of these work...help!
@{par}@{fg fill}
@{par}   -> Answered by @{"Leo Davidson" LINK "Author"}: {Qs} is like the {Qp} command. It inserts
@{par}      DOpus's public screen name into the command string. It doesn't check if
@{par}      a named public screen exists or anything like that.
@{par}
@{par}      @{b}NOTE@{ub}: You can't use {} sequenses in "command" type commands. This is a
@{par}            common misconception.
@{par}@{fg text}
@{par} · Has anyone ever had any luck installing @{"LhaDir.DOpus5" LINK "EVLhaDir"} and getting it to work
@{par}   on the first try? I found this utility quite difficult to get going - maybe
@{par}   it is just me, but for those of you who are having trouble, I've provided
@{par}   @{"some hints to help you install LhaDir.DOpus5" LINK "InstallLhaDir"}.
@{par}@{fg fill}
@{par} · DOpus will CRASH if you: select more than one icon (containing tooltypes),
@{par}   use IconInfo, select but do not edit the first tooltype in the first icon,
@{par}   select SAVE (even though nothing has been altered) and DOpus will crash -
@{par}   GURU # 8100 0005. (I accidentally found this out the hard way, but YOU have
@{par}   been warned).
@{par}
@{par} · If you have @{"CheckGuide" LINK "CheckGuide"} you can save yourself some time by adding it to DOpus
@{par}   as either a Button or User-Menu item (@{"click for an example of how to do it" LINK "DCG"}).
@{par}
@{par} · Check out @{"Jonathon Potter's tip on how to add DIF to DOpus" LINK "DIF"}.
@{par}
@{par} · Check out this great tip on @{"How to get DOpus to Parse commands" LINK "Parse"}, by @{"Leo" LINK "Author"}.
@{par}
@{par} · @{"Leo" LINK "Author"} provides an explanation of DOpus5's @{"FileTypes" LINK "Filetype"}.
@{par}
@{par}@{fg text}
@{par} If you have answers for any of these @{"I'd love to hear from you" LINK "Author"}. Or if you have
@{par} something which you would like to share with others, contact @{"me" LINK "Author"} and I'll
@{par} include it in this section.
@{par}
@{par}@{fg shine}@{b}All Users of DOpus5@{ub}: The patch for DOpus5.11 is now on Aminet (Dopus511.lha)!!@{fg text}

@ENDNODE

