@NODE "MWB" "MagicWB is © by Martin Huttenloher"
@NEXT "MWB"
@PREV "MWB"

@{par}                      @{fg shine}MagicWB is © by Martin Huttenloher@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}
@{par}                               @{b}MagicWB V2.0
@{par}                               ============@{ub}
@{par}
@{par}
@{par}The definitive WB-Enhancer no Amiga can do without. MagicWB is a full
replacement for the graphic user interface of the Workbench and has become
the standard on the Amiga.
@{par}
@{par}MagicWB 2.0 is completely restructured on a new color-allocation scheme which
more than doubles the speed of the WB and reduces chip-consumption to only a
third compared with all previous versions and also features a highly improved
color palette. MWB 2.0 introduces a never-before-seen standard for over four
dozen of new image-drawers to achieve a more diversified look on your WB.
More icons, dock-brushes, a dozen of new patterns, fonts and a AA-support
complete this special product.
@{par}
@{par}To get the 'real' look and feel of MagicWB, you should make sure that...
@{par}
@{par} · ...you have set the MagicWB-Palette. Do this by clicking on the 'ClickFor
@{par}      Colors' icon.
@{par}
@{par} · ...you have set the resolution of your Workbench to a aspect ratio near 3:4
@{par}      like 640x480, 800x600 or 1024x768.
@{par}
@{par} The demo-version can be found on Aminet biz/demo/MagicWB20d.lha.
@{par}
@{par} @{b}MagicWB is © by Martin Huttenloher.@{ub}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "LHADest" "Adding LHA with a destination file requester"
@PREV "LHADest"
@NEXT "LHADest"
@TOC "HintsTips"

@{par}    @{fg shine}How to add an LHA destination-path file-requester to a button (or menu)@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}To add an LHA command to DOpus with a destination file requester use the
@{par}following to define either a button, a menu item or a gadget:
@{par}
@{par} TYPE:      COMMAND:
@{par} @{b}------------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}@{fg fill}
@{par} @{b}AmigaDOS@{ub} - FailAt 21
@{par} @{b}AmigaDOS@{ub} - sys:c/RequestFile DRAWER={d} PATTERN=#?.(LHA|LZH) NOICONS @{b}@{fg shine}->@{ub}@{fg fill}
@{par}            PUBSCREEN=DOPUS.1 SAVEMODE >PIPE:LHA_{Qp}
@{par} @{b}AmigaDOS@{ub} - IF FAIL
@{par} @{b}AmigaDOS@{ub} - QUIT
@{par} @{b}AmigaDOS@{ub} - ENDIF
@{par} @{b}AmigaDOS@{ub} - sys:c/LHA  -r -x u "`Type PIPE:LHA_{Qp}`" {O}@{fg text}
@{par} @{b}------------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}
@{par}
@{par}Check the following flags:
@{par}
@{par} @{fg fill}· CD source
@{par} · Output to window
@{par} · Window close button@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}@{b}NOTE:@{ub} Make sure you change the @{b}sys:c/@{ub} in the last command line to point to
@{par}      the path where @{b}Lha@{ub} can be found on @{i}your@{ui} machine.
@{par}
@{par}      the @{fg shine}@{b}->@{fg text}@{ub} means @{b}continued on the next line@{ub}; however, you would @{b}type this
@{par}      all on one line@{ub}.
@{par}
@{par}      the @{b}RequestFile@{ub} command comes with OS3.x.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "LHADir" "An LHA button (or menu) which creates seperate dirs for each archive"
@PREV "LHADir"
@TOC "HintsTips"
@NEXT "LHADir"

@{par}  @{fg shine}An LHA button (or menu) which creates seperate directories for each archive@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par} TYPE:      COMMAND:
@{par} @{b}------------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}@{fg fill}
@{par} @{b}AmigaDOS@{ub} - sys:c/LHA -M x {fu} {o-}/@{fg text}
@{par} @{b}------------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}
@{par}
@{par}Check the following flags:
@{par}
@{par} @{fg fill}· Output to window
@{par} · Window close button
@{par} · CD destination@{fg text}
@{par}
@{par}@{b}NOTE:@{ub} Make sure you change the @{b}sys:c/@{ub} to point to where the Lha command
@{par}      can be found on @{i}your@{ui} machine.

@ENDNODE

